******
[2] Cholera - Yemen (Beni Yus)
Date: Sat 8 Apr 2017
Source: SAHAFAH 24 [in Arabic, trans. Mod.MM, edited]
http://www.sahafah24.net/show889068.html


The medical director of the health services and director of Abs Rural Hospital, Dr Ibrahim Aram, confirmed to the correspondent of Alishtraki Net the admission of 19 cases of cholera coming from Beni Yus province, Hajjah governorate, including one fatal case. He also revealed that they are working in very difficult conditions with regard to medical supplies and the general condition of the hospital.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-MENA
<promed-mena@promedmail.org>

[Yemen is divided into 21 governorates (muhafazah), and they can be seen on the map at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Governorates_of_Yemen. - Mod.LL]

